.TH "bc_send_request" 9 "bc_send_request" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
bc_send_request \- Send a backchannel Call on a TCP socket
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" bc_send_request
.BI "(struct rpc_rqst *req "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "req" 12
rpc_rqst containing Call message to be sent
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
xpt_mutex ensures \fIrqstp\fP's whole message is written to the socket
without interruption.

Return values:
0 if the message was sent successfully
ENOTCONN if the message was not sent
